events.name: Cloud Study Jam IIUI Islamabad
events.description:
Hello Ladies !! Do you want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Agenda:
10:00 am - 10:15 am Intro to GCP
10:15 am - 12:00 pm Hands-on qwik lab 1 & 2
12:00 pm - 12:30 pm Break
12:30 pm - 01:30 pm Hands-on qwik lab 3

Register Here: https://forms.gle/ZBwSwa5jRxpWw8F17

events.name: TensorFlow 2.0 Global Docs Sprint
events.description:
A doc sprint is a way to improve the documentation for an open-source library. We are organizing TensorFlow docs sprint to improve TensorFlow 2.0’s documentation.

TensorFlow 2.0 is a major release focused on ease of use and clarity while maintains its flexibility. Are you interesting in learning about what is new with TensorFlow 2.0?

Would you like to contribute to TensorFlow 2.0 and learn the PR and review process? You can get started by improving its documentation.

Come join us for the Global Docs Sprint at Red Buffer where you will learn how to review and create pull requests for making changes to TensorFlow documentation.

Target audience: ideally you know Machine Learning, TensorFlow or Python in order to contribute to TensorFlow docs.

Link to Register: https://bre.is/78pNEBzUT

events.name: Big Data Workshop with a Googler
events.description:
GCDC Islamabad and GDG Islamabad have collaborated with a Googler to bring you a super cool workshop on Big Data and Google Cloud Platform!

Yes, you heard that right! Usman Ali, Big Data Product Specialist at Google Norway, is flying to Pakistan to deliver this hands-on workshop.

Big Data Workshop [Participation Cost - PKR 500] (2 PM - 5 PM)
► Registrations (15-20 mins)
► Introduction to GCP and its products (20 mins)
► Machine Learning & AI (with a demo/lab on TF via Notebook AI) (60mins)
► Big Data (with a demo on BigQuery and BigQuery ML) (35mins)
► Snacks break (15 mins)

Fireside Chat With Usman Ali [No Participation Cost] [5 PM - 6 PM]
► Fireside chat (30-40 mins)
► Networking (20-30 mins)

Please note that the workshop (from 2 PM to 5 PM) has a participation cost of PKR 500 while the fireside chat (from 5 PM to 6 PM) is free.

Due to limited seating, the slots for both the sessions will be allotted on first come first-served basis. Payment details for the workshop will be shared over email with the shortlisted candidates.

Moreover, registrations are mandatory for both sessions. Our team will evaluate your responses and IF you are shortlisted, you will get the confirmation email. Anyone who has not received an email invite from our team would not be allowed inside the venue.

events.name: Fireside Chat with Usman Ali - Googler
events.description:
Fireside Chat with Usman Ali - Big Data Product Specialist from Google Norway.

Usman has over 13 years of industry experience in Big Data and Analytics domain. He is part of Google Cloud’s Big Data Product Specialist team in Northern Europe to help large Enterprises move to the Cloud. Before Google, he has worked with Teradata for 10 years on Data Warehouse, BI, CRM and other technologies typical to DWH environment.

He is originally from Pakistan, graduated from FAST Islamabad, however, he has lived and worked in Norway from the past 10 years. Besides work, he loves spending time with his family, playing squash, binge on Netflix and go on road-trips.

events.name: WTM & GDG Cloud: #IamRemarkable Workshop

ceilings. Learn more at g.co/IamRemarkable

events.name: GDG Cloud DevFest '19 Islamabad
events.description:
GDG DevFest 2019 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, codelabs, hackathon and more!

GDG DevFest is an event that brings together the developer community and tech geeks for an immersive experience focused on exploring the next generation of diverse technologies.

Cloud Devfest 2019 is arranged by GDG CLOUD Islamabad in collaboration with Women Techmakers Ambassador Irum Zahra.

For this Devfest we have invited Googlers and Google Developer Experts from different countries to our devfest. This event is a great opportunity to network and learn from these amazing people from Google. There will be hands-on workshops, technical talks, discussions as well as non technical workshops in the Agenda.

* Everyone is Welcome Here !
GDG Cloud Islamabad supports Diversity and Inclusion. We recognize the current status of our industry and we want to change it. Our goal is to enable everybody to learn and teach programming. As such, we want to enable underrepresented groups in technology to feel welcomed and help increase the diversity in technology and science.

As a small step towards increased diversity we are offering up to ten diversity tickets and limited travel grant to underrepresented groups. Women from remote areas or far away areas, transgenders & non-binary people and disabled people are invited to apply for a diversity ticket.
Write us email after filling the form to claim your ticket at [masked]

* What is GDG ?
Google Developer Groups (GDGs) are Google supported communities of developers, designer, coders and technology enthusiasts who work together to promote learning and development in the said field.

* What is GDG CLOUD ?
The first Google Developer Group for CLOUD in Pakistan. We are a local community for developers interested in resources and technologies from Google. Google supports and recognizes all GDG chapters. Our aim is to hold events and workshops around Google Technologies specially Google Cloud as part of our community building activities.

* What is Women Techmakers ?
Women Techmakers provides visibility, community, and resources for women in technology to drive innovation and participation in the field. We encourage all women contributing to the industry to participate in Women Techmakers programs and events including developers, designers, entrepreneurs, product managers, data scientists, and more. We also support all genders to participate and volunteer for our women’s-focused events and initiatives.

* Code of Conduct:
Devfest 19 is a community conference intended for networking and collaboration in the developer community.

We value the participation of each member of the GDG community and want all attendees to have an enjoyable and fulfilling experience. Accordingly, all attendees are expected to show respect and courtesy to other attendees throughout the conference and at all conference events.

To make clear what is expected, all delegates/attendees, speakers, exhibitors, organizers and volunteers at any DevFest Islamabad event are required to conform to the following Code of Conduct. Organizers will enforce this code throughout the event.

Ticket URL: http://bit.ly/devfest19islamabad
For Updates join Facebook Event Page: https://www.facebook.com/events/767108983709525/
